   {
      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "The reason I'm creating a discussion topic here is not because I'm confused how to implement this (:smile:), but because it's slightly controversial and I might be confused about the 'easy to generate' part.\r\n\r\nI think we do want `ERROR` for validation errors on blocks unconditionally, after checking proof-of-work, because significant computation time went into generating them, and miners sending them *might* be indication of a deeper problem with the network.\r\n\r\nI think this is not the case for block headers, definitely not \"bad-diffbits\" or \"proof of work failed\". We made a similar decision about transactions. They're easy to send so they should not clutter the log by default.",
      "created_at" : "2019-11-10T11:23:34Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/17421#issuecomment-552185710",
